    Demo Party 06 - Person Requester on case 08 (In Progress Complaint)
    ====================================================================

    Synthetic seed record for the case-management POC scoped application.
    This file is the SIXTH of the 8-party demo dataset; it pairs with
    sibling party 07 (Organization/Respondent on the same case 08) to
    demonstrate that the polymorphic UI Policy works correctly on
    Complaint case types - one Person row + one Organization row on the
    same case exercises BOTH conditional branches simultaneously.
    Together with parties 01 through 05 and parties 07 + 08, this record
    satisfies AAP Section 0.4.1's seed-data folder requirements for
    `seed-data/parties/`.

    The complete 8-party fixture matrix:

        Party 01 - Person      / Requester  / parent case 03 (In Progress GI)
        Party 02 - Organization/ Respondent / parent case 03 (In Progress GI)
        Party 03 - Person      / Witness    / parent case 04 (Pending GI)
        Party 04 - Person      / Requester  / parent case 05 (Resolved GI)
        Party 05 - Organization/ Respondent / parent case 05 (Resolved GI)
        Party 06 - Person      / Requester  / parent case 08 (In Progress Complaint)  ## THIS FILE
        Party 07 - Organization/ Respondent / parent case 08 (In Progress Complaint)
        Party 08 - Person      / Witness    / parent case 09 (Resolved Complaint)

    The 8-party dataset thus exercises:
      * All 2 `party_type` choice values (Person x5, Organization x3) -
        this party contributes the FIFTH of the five Person entries.
        The Person branch demonstrates that the conditional UI Policy
        at ../../ui_policy/x_[scope]_case_party_conditional_fields.xml
        correctly shows the <person> reference field and HIDES the
        <organization> reference field when party_type=Person.
      * All 3 example `role_label` values (Requester x3, Respondent x3,
        Witness x2) - this party contributes the THIRD and final
