    Lifecycle position - WHY Person / Requester / parent Complaint
    case In Progress is meaningful:
      Per AAP Section 0.5.7 the case_party schema is:
          case        - Reference -> x_[scope]_case (mandatory)
          party_type  - Choice (Person | Organization, mandatory)
          person      - Reference -> sys_user (conditional: required
                        if party_type=Person)
          organization- Reference -> core_company (conditional: required
                        if party_type=Organization)
          role_label  - String(100) (mandatory; example values
                        Requester, Respondent, Witness)

      With party_type=Person, the conditional UI Policy at
      ../../ui_policy/x_[scope]_case_party_conditional_fields.xml
      activates the Person branch:
          - Show + require <person> field (populated below with
            "x_[scope]_demo_manager")
          - Hide <organization> field (left empty below; the empty
            <organization/> element preserves the dictionary entry's
            existence while signaling no value)

      Case 08 is in In Progress status on the Complaint flow per
      ../cases/x_[scope]_case_demo_08.xml - the densest demo case
      (Critical priority + 2 active tasks + 2 parties). The case was
      filed by an external requester (the demo manager, per this
      record's <person> field) complaining about Synthetic Org Alpha's
      conduct (per party 07's <organization> field on the same case);
      the demo team's queue accepted the complaint, the manager
      assigned the demo agent, and the agent is now actively
      investigating the complaint. The <role_label>Requester</
      role_label> on this party records the demo manager as the
      EXTERNAL REQUESTER who initiated the case - the entity who
      complained. This pattern mirrors party 01 on case 03 (In
      Progress GI) where the demo manager is also the Requester; the
      same user appearing on multiple cases reflects the normal
      operational reality that one individual may file multiple
      complaints over time (or - in the demo dataset - that the
