    Authoring rules honored (per AAP Sections 0.7.1 / 0.7.2 and the
    agent prompt's ten authoring rules):

      Rule 1 - Synthetic only (AAP Section 0.7.2 NO-PII clause):
        person       = "x_[scope]_demo_manager"  (the synthetic sys_user
                       row created by ../users/sys_user_x_[scope]_demo_
                       manager.xml; the literal "demo_manager" suffix
                       makes the synthetic nature explicit; the
                       "x_[scope]_" prefix scopes the user to the POC's
                       namespace; NOT a real person's name, NOT a real
                       login identifier, NOT linked to any real-world
                       user account)
        role_label   = "Requester"  (a generic English noun describing
                       the role of the entity who FILED the case; one
                       of the three example role_label values
                       enumerated in AAP Section 0.5.7; a standard
                       term in case-management parlance with no PII
                       implication)
        organization = EMPTY  (no organization is associated with this
                       party because party_type=Person; the empty
                       <organization/> element preserves the dictionary
                       entry binding while explicitly signaling no
                       value)
        NO requester email, phone, address, SSN, or other PII-bearing
        fields are populated; the case_party schema does not include
        any free-text PII slots.

      Rule 2 - Choice value precision:
        party_type = "Person"  (exactly as registered in
                     ../../choices/sys_choice_case_party_party_type.xml;
                     the FIRST of the two party-type choice values -
                     Person, Organization; American English spelling;
                     capital P deliberate - "Person" not "person" or
                     "PERSON"; THIS VALUE IS LOAD-BEARING because the
                     conditional UI Policy at
                     ../../ui_policy/x_[scope]_case_party_conditional_
                     fields.xml branches on case-sensitive equality
                     with "Person"; a typo would break the polymorphic
                     field-visibility rule)

      Rule 3 - Conditional Field Rule (the polymorphic invariant):
        With party_type=Person, the UI Policy mandates:
          * <person> populated with a sys_user reference
            (DONE BELOW: "x_[scope]_demo_manager" resolved by user_name
            lookup)
          * <organization> empty  (DONE BELOW: empty <organization/>
            element)
        The inverse pattern is exercised by parties 02, 05, and 07
        (party_type=Organization, organization populated, person
        empty). This file establishes the canonical Person-branch
        invariant on the Complaint flow's In Progress case.

      Rule 4 - Reference resolution by stable human-readable key (AAP
              Section 0.7.2 "NO sys_id literals anywhere"):
        case   : <case display_value="CASE0000008">CASE0000008</case>
                 resolves to demo case 08 by the case table's
                 idempotent number lookup. CASE0000008 is the auto-
                 numbered value the platform generates for demo case
                 08 since cases 01 through 08 import in order with
                 the CASE0000001-format auto-number counter (case 01
                 -> CASE0000001, case 02 -> CASE0000002, ..., case 08
                 -> CASE0000008). This party's parent therefore
                 resolves to the demo case 08 record at
                 ../cases/x_[scope]_case_demo_08.xml.
        person : <person display_value="x_[scope]_demo_manager">
                 x_[scope]_demo_manager</person> resolves to the
                 synthetic demo manager by the sys_user table's
                 user_name lookup. The same user is referenced by
                 party 01 on case 03 (also a Requester) - the lookup
                 resolves to the SAME sys_user row in both files,
                 demonstrating user-on-multiple-cases pattern.

        Both cross-reference fields use the display_value attribute
        AND the element text content set to the same human-readable
        key. ServiceNow's Update Set engine resolves the target
        sys_id from this key at import time via the table's
        idempotent-key lookup. NO sys_id literals appear in any
        cross-reference slot per AAP Section 0.7.2. Note that the
        agent prompt's "Exact XML Structure" example included sys_id
        literals as illustrative placeholders for cross-reference
        targets; per AAP Section 0.7.2's absolute-precedence directive
        those literals are replaced here with their corresponding
        human-readable lookup keys (CASE0000008 for the case number,
        x_[scope]_demo_manager for the user_name, x_[scope] for the
        scope's source name) - an interpretation consistent with how
        sibling parties 07 and 08 were authored.

      Rule 5 - All mandatory case_party fields populated:
        case        - mandatory parent reference - CASE0000008
        party_type  - mandatory Choice           - "Person"
        person      - conditional Reference (required when
                      party_type=Person)         - "x_[scope]_demo_manager"
        organization- conditional Reference (NOT required when
                      party_type=Person)         - EMPTY (correct)
        role_label  - mandatory String(100)      - "Requester"
        Per AAP Section 0.5.7 case_party schema, this record populates
        every mandatory field for the Person branch and leaves only
        the organization slot empty (which is correct for Person
        rows). The conditional invariant is satisfied.

      Rule 6 - Scope binding:
        <sys_scope>   binds this party row to the scoped application
                      via the scope source name "x_[scope]" defined in
                      ../../app/sys_scope/x_[scope].xml at
                      <source>x_[scope]</source>; the display_value
                      "Case Management" matches the sys_app's human-
                      readable name.
        <sys_package> follows the same pattern with the additional
                      source="x_[scope]" attribute that is required by
                      the Update Set engine for scope-package binding.
