        every peer file uses (cases 01-10, sys_user_*, sys_user_group_*,
        sys_user_has_role_*, demo tasks 01-08, parties 07 + 08,
        dictionary entries, ACL records, role records); it is the
        scope's <source> field, NOT the scoped application's
        sys_update_name. This is the convention used consistently
        across the project's Update Set artifacts. Per AAP Section
        0.7.2's scoped-namespace-only constraint, NO global-scope
        writes occur; this record lives entirely within the x_[scope]
        scope.

      Rule 7 - Idempotency anchor:
        The party's idempotent key is the (case, party_type, role_label,
        person) tuple: (CASE0000008, Person, Requester,
        x_[scope]_demo_manager). The companion seed script
        ../../scripts/seed_demo_data.js ensureParty() helper queries
        x_[scope]_case_party by this 4-tuple BEFORE inserting; the
        action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE" attribute on the inner
        <x_[scope]_case_party> element ensures the same behavior at
        Update Set import time. The party's OWN <sys_id> below is the
